================================================================================
EXTERNAL SERVICES (RUNTIME, NO BUNDLED CODE)
================================================================================

The following external services are called at runtime via HTTPS. No source code
from these services is bundled with SAR Manager; only API calls are made.

  Open-Meteo
    License:    Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
    Usage:      Current weather conditions and 3-day forecast for IPP coordinates
    URL:        https://open-meteo.com
    Note:       Free, no API key required. Data sourced from national weather
                services including Environment Canada.

  Environment Canada — Meteorological Service of Canada (MSC)
    License:    Government of Canada Open Government Licence
                https://open.canada.ca/en/open-government-licence-canada
    Usage:      Best-effort weather alert fetch for Alberta
    URL:        https://dd.weather.gc.ca

  D4H Team Manager (Canada)
    License:    Commercial — credentials required; governed by SEASAR's
                D4H service agreement
    Usage:      Incident creation, personnel callouts, whiteboard notices,
                response tracking
    URL:        https://d4h.com

  CalTopo
    License:    Commercial — service account credentials required; governed by
                SEASAR's CalTopo service agreement
    Usage:      SAR map creation, IPP/PLS markers, ISRID probability ring features
    URL:        https://caltopo.com

  Microsoft Azure Active Directory (Entra ID)
    License:    Commercial — governed by SEASAR's Microsoft 365 / Azure agreement
    Usage:      Team member authentication (SSO via MSAL.js)
    URL:        https://azure.microsoft.com

  Overpass API (OpenStreetMap)
    License:    Open Database License (ODbL)
                https://opendatacommons.org/licenses/odbl/
    Usage:      Nearest hospital and SAR team lookups by coordinates
    URL:        https://overpass-api.de
    Note:       No OSM data is bundled or cached by this application; only
                real-time queries are made.

  OSRM (Open Source Routing Machine) — public demo server
    License:    BSD 2-Clause (server code); ODbL (road data from OpenStreetMap)
    Usage:      Drive-time estimates to nearest hospital and SAR teams
    URL:        https://router.project-osrm.org
    Note:       Public demo server. For production, consider hosting your own
                OSRM instance or subscribing to a commercial routing API.

  saralberta.ca
    License:    SAR Alberta member data — referenced as links only; no data
                is scraped or cached by this application
    Usage:      Mutual aid team proximity display (hardcoded centroids)
    URL:        https://saralberta.ca

